MARCTagCondition2: Form of item (008/23 except for formats Cartographic Materials or Vistual Materials, which uise 008/29)
RDA Registry URI:
For Monographs (not Continuing Resources)
Mint an IRI for the original manifestation (originalM) to which parts of the 008 and other fields are related.  
Relate it to the same expression of the same work as the manifestation for the reproduction described by the record (reproM) is related, with this property:  http://rdaregistry.info/Elements/m/P30136 "Has expression manifested".
Relate originalM to reproM with property http://rdaregistry.info/Elements/m/P30043 ""is electronic reproduction of manifestation of"
RDA Registry Label: is electronic reproduction of manifestation of
Justification for Mapping: By definition, use of 533 indicates a MARC record is describing a reproduction - with exception of some early records that recorded presence of a related electronic record in the print record reproduced, using this tag.  The 533 contains descriptive elements of the reproduction, but parts of the main description such as date of creation or publication describe the original reproduced, including elements of the 008.  Use the "electronic reproduction" property when record has Form fixed field "electronic" -LA 3/3/2024
Transformation Notes: Use the same "originalM" URI for all of the conditional mappings for 008 and other tags. - la 3/3/2024
Notes (Uncategorized):
These conditions do not include all "Provider neutral" records that are electronic reproductions.  533 is not included for PN unless it is for "digital master" digitization projects like Hathi Trust.  5xx fields are permitted if the reproduction is of an institution specific copy, e.g. a rare book, only with addition of $5 institution symbol.  But "Provider neutral" online records that are reproductions also are specified to have original descriptive elements in most 008 bytes except for the Form of Item byte which is "o" (online) and in 250, 264   

Mapping for PN records (distinguishable by 040 subfield $e "pn") which do not contain a 533 tag needs further analysis and may not be part of this mapping..  See https://www.loc.gov/aba/pcc/scs/documents/PN-RDA-Combined.pdf . and also OCLC's  https://www.oclc.org/bibformats/en/specialcataloging.html#providerneutralcataloging .  Instructions say to describe the original in parts of 008, 250, 264 in There does not appear to be a definitive data element indicating that a PN record is for a reproduction -- provider-neutral designation may be given to an electronic resource that does not reproduce another resource.  However, see instructions for 588 note and 776 for examples of what may be consistent language.
Unnamed: 30:
See 533 Issue https://github.com/uwlib-cams/MARC2RDA/issues/207 and Reproductions discussion https://github.com/uwlib-cams/MARC2RDA/discussions/385 

Logic based on LC pCC PS 1.11: Facsimiles and Reproductions October 23, 2014 https://www.loc.gov/aba/pcc/documents/1-11-LC-PCC-PS.docx
